  "text": "## Rust Trait Obligation Fulfillment Chain\n\n### Overview\nThe Rust trait solver fulfills trait obligations through a hierarchical system centered on the **ObligationForest** data structure, which manages the forest of pending trait obligations. The chain represents the old (traditional) trait solver architecture, with a modern new solver implementation alongside it.\n\n### Core Components\n\n#### 1. ObligationForest (rustc_data_structures/src/obligation_forest/mod.rs)\nThe **ObligationForest** is the fundamental data structure that tracks outstanding trait obligations. It:\n- Maintains a forest of obligation nodes, each with state (Pending, Waiting, Success, Error)\n- Implements obligation dependency tracking with parent-child relationships\n- Processes obligations via the `ObligationProcessor` trait (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/fulfill.rs:268)\n- Returns outcomes containing completed obligations and errors\n- Caches processed results to avoid duplicate work\n\nThe forest uses three core result types defined by `ProcessResult<O, E>`:\n- `Unchanged`: Ambiguous result, obligation stalled on type inference\n- `Changed(Vec<O>)`: Obligation satisfied with subobligations\n- `Error(E)`: Obligation failed\n\n#### 2. FulfillmentContext (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/fulfill.rs:61-104)\nThe **FulfillmentContext** is the old trait solver's main context that manages trait fulfillment:\n- Wraps an `ObligationForest<PendingPredicateObligation<'tcx>>`\n- Implements the `TraitEngine` trait (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/engine.rs:136)\n- Registers obligations via `register_predicate_obligation()`\n- Processes obligations through the `select()` method which invokes `FulfillProcessor`\n- Snapshot-aware to ensure correct context usage\n\n#### 3. FulfillProcessor (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/fulfill.rs:252-450)\nThe **FulfillProcessor** implements the `ObligationProcessor` trait and:\n- Processes each obligation in the forest by invoking trait selection\n- Implements `needs_process_obligation()` with optimizations checking stalled inference variables\n- Calls `SelectionContext.select()` for each obligation\n- Generates sub-obligations from confirmed candidates\n- Converts solver errors to fulfillment errors\n\n#### 4. SelectionContext (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/mod.rs:104-126)\nThe **SelectionContext** is the central context for trait candidate selection:\n- Maintains inference context and freshener for trait predicates\n- Tracks intercrate ambiguity causes for coherence checking\n- Implements the selection algorithm via `select()` and `candidate_from_obligation()`\n- Manages trait obligation stacks to detect cycles\n- Caches selection results for performance\n\n#### 5. Candidate Assembly (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/candidate_assembly.rs:25-100)\nThe **assemble_candidates()** method:\n- Collects all possible implementations that could satisfy a trait obligation\n- Sources candidates from:\n  - Trait aliases\n  - User-defined impl blocks\n  - Where-clause bounds\n  - Built-in traits (Copy, Clone, Sized, etc.)\n  - Projection predicates\n- Returns a `SelectionCandidateSet` with definite and ambiguous candidates\n\n#### 6. Confirmation (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/confirmation.rs:32-100)\nThe **confirm_candidate()** method:\n- Verifies that a selected candidate actually applies to the obligation\n- Unifies trait reference type parameters\n- Generates nested obligations based on the candidate type:\n  - `ImplCandidate`: Calls `confirm_impl_candidate()` to generate where-clause obligations\n  - `ParamCandidate`: Generates obligations from where-clause bounds\n  - `BuiltinCandidate`: No nested obligations\n  - `ObjectCandidate`, `ClosureCandidate`, etc.: Generate type-specific obligations\n- Returns an `ImplSource` representing the selected implementation\n\n#### 7. Impl Matching (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/_match.rs:24-117)\nThe **MatchAgainstFreshVars** structure:\n- Implements the `TypeRelation` trait to match types against fresh type variables\n- Used to check if an impl's trait reference matches an obligation\n- Approximates whether unification would succeed\n- Returns Ok if match succeeds, Err if it fails\n\n#### 8. TraitEngine & ObligationCtxt (rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/engine.rs)\nThe **TraitEngine** trait defines:\n- `register_predicate_obligation()`: Adds obligations to the engine\n- `try_evaluate_obligations()`: Processes pending obligations\n- `report_fulfillment_errors()`: Reports errors for unfulfilled obligations\n\nThe **ObligationCtxt** provides a simpler API wrapper around TraitEngine.\n\n#### 9. Error Reporting (rustc_trait_selection/src/error_reporting/traits/)\nError reporting occurs through:\n- **report_selection_error()** (fulfillment_errors.rs:57-100): Main entry point for reporting trait errors\n- **report_extra_impl_obligation()**: Reports obligations from impl items\n- **on_unimplemented**: Custom error messages from #[diagnostic] attributes\n- **suggestions**: Helpful suggestions for fixing trait errors\n\n### The Obligation Chain Flow\n\n1. **Registration**: Obligations registered via `ObligationCtxt.register_obligation()` → `TraitEngine.register_predicate_obligation()` → added to `FulfillmentContext.predicates` (ObligationForest)\n\n2. **Processing**: `FulfillmentContext.select()` calls `predicates.process_obligations(&mut FulfillProcessor)`\n\n3. **Obligation Processing**: `FulfillProcessor.process_obligation()` is called for each pending obligation\n   - Checks if obligation needs processing via `needs_process_obligation()`\n   - Calls `SelectionContext.select(obligation)`\n\n4. **Selection**: `SelectionContext.select()` → `candidate_from_obligation()` → `candidate_from_obligation_no_cache()`\n   - Checks cache, calls `assemble_candidates()` to collect candidate implementations\n   - Evaluates each candidate with `evaluate_candidate()`\n   - Selects the best candidate (if any)\n\n5. **Confirmation**: Selected candidate is confirmed with `confirm_candidate()`\n   - Unifies types and generates nested obligations\n   - Returns `Selection` (impl source)\n\n6. **Result Processing**: `ProcessResult` returned to forest\n   - `Changed(subobligations)`: Sub-obligations added to forest, parent suspended\n   - `Unchanged`: Obligation stays pending for next iteration\n   - `Error`: Obligation marked as error, backtrace recorded\n\n7. **Completion**: When all obligations resolved or errors detected, `process_obligations()` returns `Outcome` with completed obligations and errors\n\n8. **Error Reporting**: `report_selection_error()` called for unresolved errors, generating user-facing diagnostics\n\n### New Trait Solver\n\nIn parallel, the new trait solver (compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/solve/) provides a modern implementation:\n- Uses `FulfillmentCtxt` (different from old `FulfillmentContext`)\n- Implements goal-based solving rather than obligation forest\n- Used when `InferCtxt.next_trait_solver()` returns true\n- Can be enabled with `-Znext-solver` flag\n- Accessed through `InferCtxtSelectExt::select_in_new_trait_solver()`\n\nBoth solvers maintain the same public API through the `TraitEngine` trait, allowing for gradual migration."
}

